24-May-2026
-----------

Added a modified version of SINGER.  These (relatively minor) changes are based
on commit f88d6873796 of the main SINGER repository. A fork which contains the
modified source code is at: https://github.com/nspope/SINGER/tree/singer-snakemake-custom

Changes relative to main:

  - Per-site polarisation probabilities: the Polar_map struct maintains a dict
    mapping (double) position onto (double) polarisation probability. The mapping
    is passed via a text file to "-polar_map". The default value passed via the
    "-polar" flag is used whenever there is no position-value mapping.

  - The VCF reader now uses (double) instead of (int) for position. This is consistent
    with other parts of the software, where position is a floating-point. The rationale
    behind allowing fractional positions is that multiallelic sites may be modelled
    (as distinct biallelic sites) without colliding with adjacent bases.
